Super Rugby to Take Three-Week Break in 2012 for International Test Games

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-09-02T03:46:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/super-rugby-will-take-three-week-break-in-2012-for-international-tests.html
The 2012 Super Rugby competition
will take a three-week break in June to accommodate
international Test matches, tournament organizers said.  New Zealand ’s Blues and Crusaders will open the season Feb.
24 and the defending champion  Queensland Reds  take on archivals
New South Wales Waratahs a day later, according to the schedule
released today by  South Africa , New Zealand and Australia Rugby.  The season will run for 15 weeks to June 2, after which
there will be a break for the All Blacks, Springboks and
Wallabies to host touring international teams. The final three
rounds of the Super Rugby regular season will resume June 29.  “The bulk of these matches will be local derbies,” SANZAR
Chief Executive Officer Greg Peters said in a statement.  The three conference winners and three teams with the next-
best records advance to the six-team playoffs, which will start
July 20. The 2012 Super Rugby final is scheduled Aug. 4.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  